10. Definition of “Done” (for Kernel) — v0.5 refinement

The kernel is functionally complete when (in addition to prior v0.4 criteria):

Uncertainty mechanically constrains action intensity (PROBE/LIMITED/COMMIT)

Any override is:

explicitly declared in Orientation

scoped and episode-bounded

logged in ReviewRecord when used

Every Recommendation includes:

uncertainty summary

proportionate action justification

auditable provenance to Observations/Evidence/Assumptions

Change Log (ADD)

v0.5 — Uncertainty Semantics + Constitutional Overrides

Defined uncertainty representations (ordinal/bounded) without requiring probabilistic semantics.

Implemented Proportionate Action gating mechanically via ActionClass (PROBE/LIMITED/COMMIT) constrained by Impact × Reversibility × Uncertainty.

Introduced GovernanceMode (ADVISORY_ONLY default; EXTENDED_ALLOWED opt-in).

Added explicit override mechanism: scoped permissions, rationale, constraints, episode-bounded expiry.

Mandated ReviewRecord override audit entries whenever overrides are invoked.

Strengthened Recommendation requirements: uncertainty summary + proportionate action justification + override usage trace.

v0.5 Invariants (paste-ready list)

INV-UNC-001 (Uncertainty Required):
Any artifact influencing action (Interpretation, Assumption, Option, Recommendation) must declare uncertainty and confidence.

INV-UNC-002 (Option Gating Fields):
No Option is valid without impact, reversibility, uncertainty, and dependencies.

INV-ACT-001 (ActionClass Required):
Every Option must declare ActionClass ∈ {PROBE, LIMITED, COMMIT}.

INV-ACT-002 (Proportionate Action Gate):
COMMIT actions require uncertainty ≤ threshold derived from impact×reversibility and Orientation risk posture.

INV-REC-001 (Recommendation Justification):
Recommendations must include uncertainty_summary + proportionate_action_justification.

INV-OVR-001 (Override Explicitness):
If any override is used, Orientation must declare GovernanceMode=EXTENDED_ALLOWED and specify override_scope + override_rationale.

INV-OVR-002 (Override Scoping):
override_scope_used ⊆ override_scope (cannot exceed declared permissions).

INV-OVR-003 (Override Review Mandatory):
If override_used=true, ReviewRecord must include override audit entry.